Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.29,0:01:52.80,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,You were threatened and forced to help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.17,0:01:55.26,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,No one can blame you for that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.72,0:01:57.84,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:01:59.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He's our bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.51,0:02:01.10,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. You're helping, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.72,0:02:04.26,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Pick up the pace! And don't spill any of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.81,0:02:07.10,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Buccaneer! Carry those to Gate 8!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.10,0:02:07.77,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.48,0:02:11.56,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:13.40,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Shove him into the elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.74,0:02:28.71,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What... a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.12,0:02:32.88,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Push! Push!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.96,0:02:36.55,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,All right! We can do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.71,0:02:38.17,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Turret, turn to starboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:39.88,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.43,0:02:45.76,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Miles, send him away!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.01,0:02:47.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Aye, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.90,0:02:55.40,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,All right! We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.28,0:03:07.66,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,Where... am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.04,0:03:15.63,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Now! Let him have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:22.34,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Good job!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.51,0:03:25.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Now what?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.47,0:03:28.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,How do we throw him out of the gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.68,0:03:28.52,Default-alt,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,This stuff smells.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.61,0:03:44.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Move, brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.29,0:03:58.00,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! One more round!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.00,0:03:58.96,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're out of ammo!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:00.84,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:06.01,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.89,0:04:15.19,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:18.65,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It's north-blend fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.32,0:04:25.07,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,It vaporizes even in extremely low temperatures,\Nand with that, it absorbs body temperature in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.78,0:04:27.74,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, we're in the middle of a blizzard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.12,0:04:30.62,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,He'll freeze all the way to his brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.25,0:04:34.79,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,So cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.92,0:04:37.58,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,My body...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.17,0:04:42.26,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,...won't... move...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:49.14,Default,Sloth,0000,0000,0000,,What... a drag...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.98,0:05:01.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Hibernate until spring comes around, dimwit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.07,0:05:04.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Buccaneer, haul these three down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.49,0:05:05.36,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Roger!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.36,0:05:06.41,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:08.41,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-W-Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.41,0:05:10.20,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,W-W-Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.20,0:05:11.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We helped you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.78,0:05:12.41,Default-alt,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,"You were forced to."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.41,0:05:14.41,Default-alt,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that be more convenient for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.29,0:05:21.17,Default-alt,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm not letting you get away until the identity of that monster becomes clear, so be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.05,0:05:31.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.56,0:05:34.60,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,"Clang"?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:37.23,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:40.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.52,0:05:42.98,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,Yo! Did you have a nice nap?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.73,0:05:45.40,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I did, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.82,0:05:51.87,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,So I hear you saved our men.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.91,0:05:54.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:55.37,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,That'll be 100 cenz.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.58,0:05:58.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This wasn't out of gratitude?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.54,0:06:01.17,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... are there any news?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.17,0:06:03.88,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,The advance unit went to check up on that hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.88,0:06:05.88,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,They should be back any moment now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.09,0:06:09.22,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and Major Miles is at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.22,0:06:10.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:14.18,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,He's there to see the guy who was injured while fighting Scar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.81,0:06:16.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Scar is up north, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.98,0:06:18.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.14,0:06:20.44,Default,Neil,0000,0000,0000,,He's awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.44,0:06:21.77,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.36,0:06:24.19,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,You saved our buddies' lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.65,0:06:29.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You guys really care about your buddies, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.20,0:06:32.57,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We at Briggs consider ourselves a monolith.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.57,0:06:35.49,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And since you saved our buddies, that makes you one, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.50,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Then can't you let your buddy out of-
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.50,0:06:39.29,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,No can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.71,0:06:42.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You guys really are a monolith...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.46,0:06:47.80,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Scar's body wasn't found at the scene of the accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.59,0:06:51.22,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,There's a possibility he's lurking in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.64,0:06:52.80,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.22,0:06:54.55,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Good lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.55,0:06:58.81,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,First, the cat... and now we also need to search for Scar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.77,0:07:00.77,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.35,0:07:05.61,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Leave Scar to us and focus on getting better.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.61,0:07:07.03,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.65,0:07:09.95,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,I want you all to stay out of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:13.45,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,The Ishbalan is my prey.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.45,0:07:19.58,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately for you, we're not so soft as to let\Na mass murderer do whatever he wants here at Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.29,0:07:23.04,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We believe in the survival of the fittest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.29,0:07:28.51,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,If you let your guard down for a second, you die. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.26,0:07:32.30,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Talk shit again, and you'll never be able to leave the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.93,0:07:38.56,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We at Briggs have been commanded to take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.35,0:07:40.89,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,So stay put.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.69,0:07:48.57,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I remember. Ishbalans are so interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.07,0:07:54.66,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Are you doing all right, Kimblee?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.32,0:07:59.16,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,You got here sooner than I'd expected, Lieutenant General Raven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:08:01.66,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I rushed here after I heard about your injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.66,0:08:03.67,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,You had me worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:07.88,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,This is what you're worried about, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.01,0:08:12.55,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.55,0:08:14.01,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Now, time to get to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.34,0:08:16.97,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,But as you can see, I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.39,0:08:21.27,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a doctor well-versed in alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:23.27,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,And we have the stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.77,0:08:25.77,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be well in no time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.49,0:08:38.78,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Eastern Alchemy is quite difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.03,0:08:42.54,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Especially this whole concept of the "veins of the dragon".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.00,0:08:44.79,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,It's to describe the power running through the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.50,0:08:46.79,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Power running through the earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:49.92,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Simply put,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.92,0:08:56.01,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,it's a power that goes back into the ground after erupting from the summit of a mountain, and enriches the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.01,0:08:59.80,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as a river that runs through the earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.31,0:09:04.64,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,By understanding that flow of strength, its entrances and exits...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.40,0:09:11.69,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,You can apply it to practically anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.48,0:09:15.20,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,When you say "anything", does this apply to the human body, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.90,0:09:17.20,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.20,0:09:19.12,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,For example... your hip!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.45,0:09:21.91,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,My foot...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:23.95,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Or, right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.71,0:09:29.04,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Why did I feel that in my eyes after having my neck pressed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.04,0:09:32.13,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,You need to take care of your body, Dr. Marcoh.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.13,0:09:34.71,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,The power in your body is stagnant in many places.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.51,0:09:37.30,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I-I see now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.30,0:09:40.22,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So this is what makes long-distance transmutation possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.97,0:09:44.98,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,So your alchemy doesn't use the veins of the dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.23,0:09:49.19,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We use the energy created by tectonic movements.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.19,0:09:54.23,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,The immense amount of energy that is released by earthquakes and volcanic activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.48,0:09:58.03,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,This country's alchemy uses that energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:10:00.24,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.12,0:10:05.12,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since I stepped foot in this country, I felt like something was out of place...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:08.37,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,I finally realized what once I went underground in Central...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.92,0:10:11.88,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...but this power, which flows beneath our feet...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.63,0:10:15.46,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...feels more like it's coming from thousands of people squirming about...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.88,0:10:22.55,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,...rather than energy created by tectonic movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.31,0:10:33.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.82,0:10:36.44,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,A platoon should be able to get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.44,0:10:39.70,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The tunnel goes on indefinitely, following a loose curve.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.49,0:10:42.95,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But there aren't any signs of people down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.74,0:10:45.99,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Take the horses down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:47.16,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.16,0:10:48.79,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And bring those three, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.21,0:10:56.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wow... It really is huge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.21,0:11:01.43,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we let him break in without noticing all this was going on...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.43,0:11:04.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the first time Briggs has been invaded?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.97,0:11:06.72,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Since I came here, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.39,0:11:12.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,But around twenty years ago, there was a case when our security guards were attacked during midwinter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.44,0:11:17.90,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, a mysterious woman kept stealing food and supplies from them for an entire month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.82,0:11:21.99,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I survived in Briggs in the winter for a month!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.99,0:11:23.62,Default,Both,0000,0000,0000,,It has to be her...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.58,0:11:28.12,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this is far enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.75,0:11:29.95,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.17,0:11:33.12,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.46,0:11:36.13,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to worry about anyone eavesdropping on us down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.71,0:11:39.13,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me everything you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.84,0:11:41.13,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I mean everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.63,0:11:44.22,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hide anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.89,0:11:50.27,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked you about the monster, you asked me to try to realize your situation, did you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.39,0:11:55.86,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,More or less, you believed that I would realize your situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:12:01.90,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You could have been killed at any time in that situation, yet you still summoned those words.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.32,0:12:05.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So I figured you had something to protect,\Neven if it meant you'd lose your life doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.07,0:12:07.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,For example, a hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:12.91,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to cut the bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.21,0:12:14.71,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.59,0:12:21.26,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We need your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.05,0:12:28.43,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Philosopher's stones... Homunculi...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:33.14,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,King Bradley, and a man who is referred to as Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.14,0:12:35.40,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,And the entire upper echelon is guilty....
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.85,0:12:38.11,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,So as we thought, people were being taken hostage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:42.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,A friend of yours who is an automail mechanic and Mustang's men...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.15,0:12:48.87,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We performed many joint drills with Eastern Headquarters, so I know Hawkeye and Havoc.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.53,0:12:51.62,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It would be a big loss to lose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.00,0:12:53.29,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.75,0:12:56.58,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... what about Colonel Mustang?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.58,0:13:00.21,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... I don't really care about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.71,0:13:05.05,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It would actually be better for me if he just falls, so I have one less rival to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:09.55,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, we need to decide what to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:13.22,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,How do you alchemists see this underground path?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.15,0:13:26.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think this tunnel was dug from Drachma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.11,0:13:33.04,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,This is only a hypothesis, but it seems as though this tunnel was dug to create a large circle.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.04,0:13:33.83,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,A circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:39.83,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A circle governs the circulation of power in alchemy and is an important factor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.96,0:13:42.59,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now, for the equation...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.67,0:13:50.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant Falman, do you know the major incidents within the country that resulted in a lot of bloodshed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.35,0:13:51.47,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Bloodshed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.35,0:13:54.81,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,How would that...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.44,0:14:04.23,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Riviere Incident in July of 1558.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.23,0:14:06.49,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Riviere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.90,0:14:11.62,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The civil war in Cameron in October of 1661.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.45,0:14:16.29,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Soapman incident, February 1799.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.29,0:14:17.71,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,That happened in Fisk.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.71,0:14:22.25,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Wellsley Conflict, March 1811.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.84,0:14:29.26,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The First Southern Border Conflict occurred in\NOctober of 1835, northwest of where South City is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.09,0:14:35.14,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Second Southern Border Conflict happened in May of 1911, just south of Fortsett.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.85,0:14:37.27,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,What about Pendleton to the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:41.77,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Many soldiers have died there in the battles against Creta, a neighboring nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.15,0:14:46.40,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,And the riot in Liore, in 1914.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.40,0:14:47.78,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Severe casualties.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.99,0:14:49.03,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Wai-
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.03,0:14:51.11,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,A riot?! Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.61,0:14:57.54,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't we report the situation to Eastern Headquarters immediately after we exposed the fake priest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.54,0:14:58.96,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,It was the Central army.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.54,0:15:03.17,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,They came and made the Eastern army withdraw.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.17,0:15:06.50,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Liore turned into a mess after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.50,0:15:07.80,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.80,0:15:08.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.72,0:15:11.26,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Continue what you were doing earlier, Fullmetal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:14.68,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.85,0:15:21.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Now we're going to connect the dots.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.11,0:15:25.32,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,How could this be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.52,0:15:29.65,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,It's almost identical to the transmutation circle we found under Research Laboratory 5!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.70,0:15:34.32,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,A circle for creating a philosopher's stone, which uses human lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.62,0:15:39.58,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Just how many people will die with such a large transmutation circle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.58,0:15:46.59,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,I once asked Envy if they were trying to create a philosopher's stone using this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:52.59,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But he laughed and told me I was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.18,0:16:00.60,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,In the past, I told Edward that he'd surely be able to realize the real truth, which lies beyond the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.27,0:16:06.11,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,What I meant by the "truth" was that the stones are made of live humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.69,0:16:11.24,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,And what I meant by "beyond the truth" is the existence of the ones behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.44,0:16:17.24,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,And the truth beyond the truth is the transmutation of a philosopher's stone using the entire nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.24,0:16:20.20,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not where it ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.20,0:16:23.96,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what they're planning to do in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.62,0:16:27.25,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We also don't know about immortality, which is what you're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.88,0:16:31.01,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,So you mustn't long for a philosopher's stone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.80,0:16:38.81,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx99}We must decipher this research by combining my knowledge of alchemy and your knowledge of Eastern Alchemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.81,0:16:39.76,Default,May,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.39,0:16:47.77,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,The oldest one was in 1558...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.36,0:16:50.73,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Right after Amestris was founded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:56.11,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Without even a declaration of war, Amestris invaded Riviere, which was once a neighboring country...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.78,0:16:57.53,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.16,0:17:00.54,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:03.96,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The military is involved in every one of these incidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.16,0:17:08.88,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The coup d'etat... the civil wars... and Liore, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.34,0:17:12.42,Default,Fal,0000,0000,0000,,The Central Army came out and poured oil on the flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.09,0:17:14.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since this nation was created?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.93,0:17:23.06,Default,Oil,0000,0000,0000,,Our country started out as a small nation, but we expanded by annexing the small countries around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.10,0:17:25.81,Default,Oil,0000,0000,0000,,So it was to create this circle?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.15,0:17:36.07,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So it wasn't their plan to use this country to do something, but they created this country to realize their task.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.20,0:17:38.49,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Our country...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.78,0:17:43.91,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,So, Mr. Hughes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.91,0:17:48.33,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He saw the transmutation circle for the stone before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.13,0:17:54.17,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}Since he worked in the building they have strategy meetings in,\Nhe had access to more resources than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.55,0:17:58.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He was the first to realize there was something wrong with this country-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.14,0:18:02.26,Default,Isaac,0000,0000,0000,,Dog of the military. State Alchemist!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.26,0:18:06.43,Default,Isaac,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any idea what this country is trying to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.43,0:18:11.81,Default,Envy,0000,0000,0000,,Do you really think all this prosperity was created with the powers of humans only?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.81,0:18:15.82,Default,Isaac,0000,0000,0000,,If you {\i1}did{\fscx30} {\r} know, you'd understand why I'm doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.20,0:18:19.53,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.74,0:18:24.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at the pattern, the next area that will see bloodshed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.41,0:18:28.75,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,The only area left is Briggs!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:33.29,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,What do those pigs at Central plan to do with my castle?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.29,0:18:34.71,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major General!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.17,0:18:37.05,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Please return to base at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.05,0:18:39.72,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant General Raven has come to visit from Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.59,0:18:43.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So they're not even giving us time to think, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.93,0:18:46.35,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Armstrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.68,0:18:49.73,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,There's something I'd like to ask of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.69,0:18:55.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Could you try and trick Lieutenant General Raven?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.15,0:19:02.07,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for making you wait, Lieutenant General Raven.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.62,0:19:04.24,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,No, worry not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.74,0:19:06.87,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,It's my fault for coming here without advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.75,0:19:10.29,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Armstrong will be back shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.29,0:19:11.25,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Please, follow me-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:12.17,Default-alt,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.54,0:19:14.13,Default-alt,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought a guest with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.54,0:19:18.88,Default-alt,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles, do you mind giving him a tour of the fort?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.09,0:19:22.97,Default,Kim,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.02,0:19:30.85,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Winry's apple pie.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.19,0:19:35.11,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The thing I said I'd like to eat when I get my body back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.11,0:19:39.82,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we have more important things to think about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.61,0:19:43.28,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, you'll be able to eat it someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.45,0:19:50.96,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,After we get our bodies back and beat the crap out of those guys planning to use this country for their own goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.66,0:19:52.67,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.00,0:19:56.67,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the mess, Lieutenant General.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.92,0:19:59.13,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We were attacked by the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.13,0:20:00.17,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Attacked?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.84,0:20:05.97,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to drive it off,\Nbut the thing was... what you'd call a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:08.76,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.72,0:20:11.93,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't die no matter what we did to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.93,0:20:13.56,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.35,0:20:16.44,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.69,0:20:23.20,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Personally, I think it's a biological weapon from Drachma, but the Elric Brothers...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.61,0:20:29.04,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,We've taken in the Fullmetal Alchemist and his younger brother by chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.99,0:20:34.92,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It seems as though they know something about the monster but won't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.83,0:20:43.47,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx98}It could be a disaster if a state alchemist who works with the Führer President is a Drachman spy, so we've arrested them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.47,0:20:45.05,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.55,0:20:47.43,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.64,0:20:50.39,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,They really won't say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.81,0:20:51.43,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.02,0:20:56.19,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They also claim they came here to research organic transmutation or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.19,0:21:00.44,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,They're being quite ambiguous. I couldn't doubt them more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.99,0:21:10.16,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I thought about torturing it out of them, but I'm technically a woman, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.70,0:21:12.58,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't lay a finger on a child like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.58,0:21:15.08,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,My heart would be crushed...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:16.75,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:19.59,Default,Bucca,0000,0000,0000,,That queen's made of ice to the core.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.67,0:21:27.01,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,So even you, who holds the title of "The Northern Wall of Briggs", has a soft spot for children, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.76,0:21:36.10,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be odd to have a child or two at my age,\Nbut I'm totally behind in those affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:37.81,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.81,0:21:39.81,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,You must be much sought after by the men.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.15,0:21:41.11,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.94,0:21:45.61,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It's such a sad experience to age, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.07,0:21:48.86,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm absolutely horrified of aging.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.53,0:21:54.12,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,That biological weapon from Drachma had a wonderful body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.25,0:21:56.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,An immortal body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.46,0:21:59.21,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it like a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.46,0:22:07.34,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,What if I were to tell you that it may not be long before it isn't just a dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.27,0:22:16.68,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Major General...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.81,0:22:21.69,Default,Raven,0000,0000,0000,,Are you interested in a perfect, immortal army?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.90,0:22:23.36,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,He fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.45,0:24:00.08,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,"Obey the ones with power".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.08,0:24:02.46,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,That's the true meaning of the law of the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.46,0:24:08.25,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx98}If you don't wish to be bound by that, obtain greater power.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.25,0:24:13.63,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx94}Because there's always times one must fight power with power.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.39,0:24:18.47,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.47,0:24:21.85,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 36, Family Portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.98,0:24:26.48,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Men set out on journeys with determination in their hearts.
